Package org.botblock.javabotblockapi.requests

Class GetAction

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.botblock.javabotblockapi.requests.GetAction
  • @Deprecated
@DeprecatedSince(version="5.0.0",
                 replacements={"GetBotAction","GetListAction"})
public class GetAction
extends Object
    Deprecated.
    Use GetBotAction for Bot related and GetListAction for List related actions.
    Class to perform GET actions with.

    With this class can you retrieve information about either a bot, its information on the bot lists, or the bot lists themself.

    All requests are cached for 2 minutes. This can be disabled with GetAction(true) although it's not recommended.

    Since:
    3.0.0

        public GetAction​(boolean disableCache)
        Deprecated.
        Constructor to get the instance of GetAction. Use this if you want to disable the caching of the GET requests. We do not recommend this without own caching/ratelimiting.
        Parameters:
        disableCache - Whether or not caching should be disabled. true means caching is disabled!

    • Method Detail

      • getBotInfo

        @Nullable
public @Nullable JSONObject getBotInfo​(Long id)
        Deprecated.
        Gets the full information of a bot.

        The JSONObject may look like this: 

        
 {
     "id": "123456789012345678",
     "username": "MyBot",
     "discriminator": "1234",
     "owners": [
         "234567890123456789"
     ],
     "server_count": 100,
     "invite":"https://discordapp.com/oauth2/authorize?client_id=123456789012345678&scope=bot",
     "list_data": {
         "somebotlist.com": [
             {"data": "Unique bot list data"},
             200
         ],
         "otherlist.org": [
             {"data": "Unique bot list data"},
             404
         ]
     }
 }

        The values of id, username, discriminator, owners, server_count and invite are based on the most common appearance.
        The returned information from the different bot list may vary for each one.
        Parameters:
        id - The bots id to use.
        Returns:
        Possibly-null JSONObject containing the bots information.

      • getBotList

        @Nullable
public @Nullable JSONObject getBotList​(@NotNull
                                       @NotNull String id,
                                       @NotNull
                                       @NotNull Site site)
        Deprecated.
        Gets the API information of a specific bot list on botblock.org.

        The returned JSON could look like this: 

        
 {
   "api_docs": "https://thelist.org/api/docs",
   "api_post": "https://thelist.org/api/bot/stats/:id",
   "api_field": "server_count",
   "api_shard_id": "shard_id",
   "api_shard_count": "shard_count",
   "api_shards": null,
   "api_get": "https://thelist.org/api/bot/info/:id"
 }
        Parameters:
        id - The id used for the internal caching.
        site - The site to get information from.
        Returns:
        Possibly-null JSONObject containing information from the provided bot list.

        @Nullable
public @Nullable JSONObject getBotLists​(@NotNull
                                        @NotNull String id)
        Deprecated.
        Gets the API information of all supported bot lists on botblock.org.

        The returned JSON could look like this: 

        
 {
   "thelist.org": {
     "api_docs": "https://thelist.org/api/docs",
     "api_post": "https://thelist.org/api/bot/stats/:id",
     "api_field": "server_count",
     "api_shard_id": "shard_id",
     "api_shard_count": "shard_count",
     "api_shards": null,
     "api_get": "https://thelist.org/api/bot/info/:id"
   },
   "listofbots.com": {
     "api_docs": "https://listofbots.com/docs",
     "api_post": "https://listofbots.com/api/stats/:id",
     "api_field": "guild_count",
     "api_shard_id": null,
     "api_shard_count": null,
     "api_shards": "shards",
     "api_get": null
   }
 }
        Parameters:
        id - The id used for the internal caching.
        Returns:
        A Possibly-null JSONObject containing information from all supported bot lists.

      • getBotListFeatures

        public JSONArray getBotListFeatures​(@NotNull
                                    @NotNull String id,
                                    @NotNull
                                    @NotNull Site site)
        Deprecated.
        Gets the features of a bot list.
        The displayed features of a bot list can be both positive and negative.

        The returned JSONArray may look like this: 

        
 [
     {
         "name": "Markdown Long Description",
         "id": 4,
         "display": 4,
         "type": 0,
         "description": null,
         "value": 1
     },
     {
         "name": "Certified Bot Invite Link",
         "id": 18,
         "display": 3,
         "type": 0,
         "description": null,
         "value": 1
     }
 ]
        Parameters:
        id - The id used for the internal caching.
        site - The site to get information from.
        Returns:
        JSONArray containing various information about the specified bot list.
        Since:
        4.3.0
